{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"sgxlnynp7wmo4nqyldvdjbm","title":"Cloudwave","desc":"","updated":1683722216616,"created":1683722185654,"custom":{},"fname":"cloudwave","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"2f4bd41749fbd287c2b30d5d58ff6e01","links":[],"anchors":{"concept":{"type":"header","text":"Concept","value":"concept","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"components":{"type":"header","text":"Components","value":"components","line":15,"column":0,"depth":1},"build-images":{"type":"header","text":"Build Images","value":"build-images","line":16,"column":0,"depth":2},"store-and-cache-images":{"type":"header","text":"Store and cache images","value":"store-and-cache-images","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"4mmrte35ar3p4u8s8iba1k3","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"cloudwave\">Cloudwave<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#cloudwave\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"concept\">Concept<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#concept\"></a></h1>\n<p>The center of our Infrastructure should be a Node JS API running some backend framework. When a specific route is called (\"/deploy\") the backend should check if a git URL was supplied and the framework type was also present in a separate field. </p>\n<p>It should then start a dagger pipeline for the framework given, that fetches the repo, builds a container for it and stores it in a local registry. If possible it could then also deploy the container to a k0s cluster. But this could also be handled separately with the k0s SDK. </p>\n<p>Later this could be expanted with seceret management and so on.</p>\n<h1 id=\"components\">Components<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#components\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"build-images\">Build Images<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#build-images\"></a></h2>\n<p>It is important to safly build the images in an isolated env</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/genuinetools/img\">https://github.com/genuinetools/img</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"store-and-cache-images\">Store and cache images<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#store-and-cache-images\"></a></h2>\n<p>Right now im unsure how this is going to work</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/registry/deploying/\">https://docs.docker.com/registry/deploying/</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"4mmrte35ar3p4u8s8iba1k3","title":"Cloudwave","desc":"","updated":1683722200036,"created":1683710328112,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"fdc952c5cfe5dda00ebc18591251c761","links":[],"anchors":{"cloudwave-documentation":{"type":"header","text":"Cloudwave Documentation","value":"cloudwave-documentation","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["sgxlnynp7wmo4nqyldvdjbm"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"#  Cloudwave Documentation\n\nWe're thrilled that you've chosen our one-click deployment PaaS platform to deploy your applications and are excited to provide you with the resources you need to get started quickly and easily. üíªüöÄ\n\nOur documentation tools are designed to provide you with comprehensive guidance on how to use CloudWave, from setting up your account to deploying your first application. üìöüîç\n\nWhether you're new to cloud computing or an experienced developer, we're here to help you every step of the way. So dive in, explore our documentation, and get ready to ride the wave of cloud deployment! üåäüèÑ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è\n\n\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelfContainedVaults":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none"